{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"03475003-664e-436d-9db4-799d92278c59","content":"This single file gives you the biggest improvement. `Directory.Build.rsp` is automatically picked up by MSBuild — no code changes needed.\n\n### Summary of recommendations\n\n| Fix | How | Impact |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Node reuse** | `Directory.Build.rsp` with `-nodeReuse:true` (done above) | ⭐⭐⭐ Eliminates process startup overhead by keeping MSBuild nodes alive between builds |\n| **`dotnet watch build`** | Use instead of repeated `dotnet build` | ⭐⭐⭐ Keeps MSBuild warm + auto-rebuilds on file change — ideal for edit-build-test loops |\n| **MSBuild Server** | Set env var `DOTNET_CLI_USE_MSBUILD_SERVER=1` | ⭐⭐ Experimental in .NET 8; reuses a persistent MSBuild server process across invocations |\n\nThe `Directory.Build.rsp` file is the most impactful no-friction fix — it makes `dotnet build` behave like VS by reusing MSBuild worker nodes, cutting incremental no-op builds from 2–4s down to sub-second.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b4e5d594-8f12-479c-bd71-cae44efce9f8","outputTokens":286,"requestId":"280C:12EB87:5C439A1:63BBC05:69FBE294"},"id":"f92f01b2-adff-402b-8465-6e1999257c54","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:53:48.941Z","parentId":"07719e84-4d4c-4eb4-9905-83843fefe5fa"}
